On Fri, Feb 25, 2000 at 01:17:57PM -0500, Mike A. Harris wrote:
> I'm wondering what you all do to minimize the amount of disk
> space it takes to be mucking with the kernel?
You could just keep the trees in a local CVS. That way you can have
different branches for each of your workings, and still be able to diff
against a pristine cvs branch.
